Combine garlic powder, salt, and pepper in small bowl. Slice tofu in thin strips. Rub spices into tofu strips. Cover, and refrigerate for 2 days. Preheat oven to 115 degrees F (45 degrees C), or lowest oven setting. Line oven rack with foil, and place rack in lowest oven position. Place tofu strips directly on foil. Bake for 6 to 8 hours.